  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Rat Swarm",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png",
            "name": "Additional Lore",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "bubonic plague",
              "aonid": 6,
              "game-obj": "Diseases",
              "name": "bubonic plague",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Rats and Disease",
          "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
          "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "1.1",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "1.1",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 288",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core pg. 288",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core",
              "page": 288,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "Rats have a reputation of being vicious, aggressive animals that attack food stores in great numbers and spread disease. While rats are immune to the most severe effects of their own putrid plague, the disease makes them unpredictable and aggressive. Some populations of rats carry even more deadly diseases, such as bubonic plague.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "errata": {
            "alt": "1.1",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "1.1",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core pg. 288",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core pg. 288",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core",
          "page": 288,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "A swarm of rats can cause total chaos within a household or business. Contracting putrid plague is all the easier when dozens of these agitated or hungry vermin gather to bite victims en masse, making rat-hunting a viable career in many parts of the world as desperate townspeople seek relief from the disease's spread.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
